\begin_layout Standard
If the current location of the agent is not covered by any cell, i.e., 
\begin_inset Formula $\vert C_{m}\vert=0$
\end_inset

, the step set 
\begin_inset Formula $SS_{0}$
\end_inset

 is applied (see Algorithm
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "alg:07-Agent_step_set_0"

\end_inset

).
 At the beginning, the cell with the lowest path loss, 
\begin_inset Formula $c'$
\end_inset

, that may cover a UE at this location, is selected.
 If several cells have the same 
\begin_inset Formula $l_{cm}^{\downarrow}$
\end_inset

 value, one of them is randomly chosen.
 Once 
\begin_inset Formula $c'$
\end_inset

 is uniquely identified, the agent changes its pilot power by 
\begin_inset Formula $inc\_rate$
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

dB.
\end_layout

