\begin_layout Standard
Using a higher 
\begin_inset Formula $inc\_rate$
\end_inset

 than 
\begin_inset Formula $dec\_rate$
\end_inset

 reflects the behavior of the agents when full coverage of the service area
 is not guaranteed.
 In practice, areas without service coverage usually appear as irregular
 islands.
 The stopping criteria were set by limiting the total number of pilot-power
 changes an agent is allowed to make.
 The value was set to 10,000, even though for some of the test networks
 the best solutions were found in the first quarter of the experiment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All experiments were performed on a multi-core Intel i7 2.67
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

GHz desktop computer with 6
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

GB of RAM running a 64-bit Linux operating system.
 The GPU hardware used was an ATI HD5570 with 1
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

GB of DDR3 RAM.
 The implementation language used was C, combined with OpenCL and OpenMPI
 extensions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Results
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The results achieved by the parallel-agent approach, listed in Table
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:06-Optimization_results"

\end_inset

, improved the optimization objective significantly.
 They show that the pilot-power usage was reduced in all networks while
 the service area was kept under full coverage.
 Moreover, the parallel-agent solution for Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{1}$
\end_inset

 improved the attenuation-based setting by more than 300%.
 As for Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{2}$
\end_inset

, the observed improvement is around 232%, while the improvement for Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{3}$
\end_inset

 is more than 170%.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The last test network, Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{6}$
\end_inset

, is the same as N6 in
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Siomina:Minimum.pilot.power.for.service.coverage"

\end_inset

.
 When comparing these results to those of
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Siomina:Minimum.pilot.power.for.service.coverage"

\end_inset

, an improvement of almost 3% can be observed in the solution provided by
 the parallel-agent approach, i.e., 0.778 against 0.759 for the average pilot
 power of Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{6}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float table
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Optimization results after applying two different approaches for solving
 the service-coverage problem.
 All values are expressed in Watts.
\emph on

\begin_inset CommandInset label
