\begin_layout Subsection
Performance analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The graphs shown in Figures
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:06-Convergence_Net1"

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:06-Convergence_Net2"

\end_inset

 and
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:06-Convergence_Net3"

\end_inset

 depict the convergence of the parallel-agent approach after ten independent
 runs for test networks Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{1}$
\end_inset

, Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{2}$
\end_inset

 and Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{3}$
\end_inset

, respectively.
 Only feasible solutions were plotted, i.e., the solutions that meet the full-cove
rage constraint.
 Unfeasible solutions were marked with a value of inferior quality than
 the worst solution found: 428 for Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{1}$
\end_inset

, 129 for Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{2}$
\end_inset

, and 1,435 for Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{3}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From the graphs of Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{1}$
\end_inset

 (see Figure
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:06-Convergence_Net1"

\end_inset

) and Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{2}$
\end_inset

 (see Figure
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:06-Convergence_Net2"

\end_inset

), a good initial convergence can be observed.
 This is followed by a steady improvement of the intermediate solutions.
 In Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{1}$
\end_inset

, no additional solution improvement is noticed towards the end of the optimizat
ion process.
 This fact suggests that the stopping criteria is suitable for this problem
 instance.
 A similar situation is observed for Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{2}$
\end_inset

, that also shows a flat profile towards the end.
 From the graph of Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{3}$
\end_inset

 (see Figure
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:06-Convergence_Net3"

\end_inset

), a slower initial convergence, followed by a steady improvement of intermediat
e solutions and no significant solution enhancement towards the end, can
 be observed.
 This convergence profile suggests that this problem instance presents a
 more difficult optimization case than for Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{1}$
\end_inset

 and Net
\begin_inset Formula $_{2}$
\end_inset

.
 Indeed, this is the largest test network in terms of surface area.
 However, further investigation is needed to confirm this hypothesis.
 Nevertheless, the parallel-agent approach improved the pilot-power usage
 of this test network by almost 75%.
\end_layout

